    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03234.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">New Haven Conn:<ptr target="loc.03234_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1885-07-01">July 1, 1885</date>
                    <name type="place"><hi rend="underline">PO Box 489</hi></name>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Whitman:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> I see by the papers that you may be going to England. If you go you must see <choice><abbr>W<hi
                    rend="superscript">m</hi></abbr><expan>William</expan></choice> Bell Scott,<ptr target="n0547"/> the painter and poet,
                the first (unless, Dante Rossetti<ptr target="n0521"/> were earlier) of your English
                admirers. He will be glad to welcome you. And I glad to give you a note of
                introduction when I know you are going. We are old friends and regular
                correspondents, and I had much delightful time with him in England and Scotland
                during 1883 and '84, being then across the water. </p>
            <p> You will tell me too if I can be of other use to you. I may <pb xml:id="leaf001v"
                    facs="loc.03234.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/> be visiting the dear old
                    land again next year, probably having to look after the bringing out of a book&#8212;on Wood Engraving.</p>
            <p> As I am writing I think of something to send you, which ought to have come to you
                before. It is a bit of home-production, setting up, printing, binding and all.
                You'll not value it less for that. </p>
            <p> Need I say that I am glad to see a good report of your health and that, however
                drifted off&#8212;as seems too generally our human fate&#8212;I am always pleased to think of
                you. Let me hear from you and believe me always </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>heartily yours</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">WJ Linton</hi></signed>
            </closer> 

